<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murdock &amp; C. W. Chen" authorityYear="2020" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana decipiens" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ptisana decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(deceiving or misleading) refers to the morphological variation that has misled people into thinking two species were present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
